description:
Brand new one bedroom apartment in a brownstone in the Bedford-Stuyvesant/Bushwick border neighborhood. One full-size bed in the bedroom and one convertible couch in the living room which can sleep another two people with a brand new kitchen and bath. The apartment is within walking distance to great restaurants in south Bushwick and Stuyvesant Heights. Saraghina, Peaches, etc. JMZ and the G train are both walkable with easy access to Manhattan. 30 minutes to the Lower East Side/Downtown.

One bedroom with a full-size bed and a fold out, full-size bed in the living room. Brand new kitchen and bath.

You have access to the whole apartment.

These spots are walking distance
Burley Coffee- coffee shop
Vin De Table - great wines
Skytown BK- coffee, drinks, food
Birdy's Bushwick- drinks
Bizarre Bushwick- drinks/food
Lover's Rock NYC- drinks
Happy Fun Hideaway- gay bar
Flowers for all occasions- coffee/drinks
Peaches- soul food
Eugene and Company- great brunch
Oaxaca Tacos- tacos/mexican
Saraghina- great Italian and a nice coffee shop and bakery connected
Chez Oskar- bistro/french
Casablanca Brooklyn- drinks + music
Physical Culture Collective- Muy Thai Boxing and Jiu Jitsu
Namastuy- Yoga and Massage
Sacred Brooklyn- Hot Yoga and Dance
Richie's Gym- muscle daddy gym
Local Honey BK- great place for mani/pedi
Foster's Sundry- fancy meats and cheese, coffee, lunch

A short walk to the J,M train Myrtle Ave stop and the G train Nostrand stop. 30 minutes to the Lower East Side on the JM, 15 minutes (1 stop on the express) to Williamsburg, BK.
